abstract: Ms. Warren has hired about 50 people in Iowa, giving her a head start at organizing for next year’s caucuses. But it’s a strategy loaded with risk.
snippet: Ms. Warren has hired about 50 people in Iowa, giving her a head start at organizing for next year’s caucuses. But it’s a strategy loaded with risk.
lead_paragraph: WEST DES MOINES, Iowa — It was game time at the “Persist Party.”

abstract: Seventeen candidates have already qualified for the first debate. Here is a look at how the party will decide who makes the stage if that number passes 20.
snippet: Seventeen candidates have already qualified for the first debate. Here is a look at how the party will decide who makes the stage if that number passes 20.
lead_paragraph: During the 2016 presidential primary, leaders of the Democratic National Committee were frequently accused of showing favoritism toward Hillary Clinton over Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont. Perhaps as a result, party officials have tried to make the 2020 primary process appear more inclusive and transparent.

abstract: A blizzard of tweets by the president suggested he was anxious about Mr. Biden’s appeal with union workers, especially in the Midwest.
snippet: A blizzard of tweets by the president suggested he was anxious about Mr. Biden’s appeal with union workers, especially in the Midwest.
lead_paragraph: Two days after Joseph R. Biden Jr. defined his 2020 campaign as a mission to take back blue-collar voters, his close relationship with unions was already getting under the skin of President Trump, as the two men tussle over labor support in crucial Midwestern swing states.

abstract: As income inequality becomes a central issue for Democrats, two plans offered by Mr. Booker and Ms. Harris offer a proxy of the battle between them.
snippet: As income inequality becomes a central issue for Democrats, two plans offered by Mr. Booker and Ms. Harris offer a proxy of the battle between them.
lead_paragraph: LONDONDERRY, N.H. — On his third trip to New Hampshire recently, Senator Cory Booker had a new and very specific focus: his “baby bonds” proposal to combat income inequality by giving every child a government-funded savings account.

abstract: “‘Make America Moral Again’ is a nice sentiment, but it is an absolutely terrible hat,” Jimmy Kimmel said of Joe Biden’s answer to the Trump slogan.

abstract: Mr. Biden is trying to stay above the intraparty fray, invoking his years with Obama. Mr. Sanders is taking direct aim at the former vice president.
snippet: Mr. Biden is trying to stay above the intraparty fray, invoking his years with Obama. Mr. Sanders is taking direct aim at the former vice president.
lead_paragraph: MONTICELLO, Iowa — On his first trip to Iowa in his third bid for the presidency, Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Tuesday accused President Trump of coddling white supremacists, called former President Barack Obama “an extraordinary man” and vowed fidelity to longstanding Democratic priorities like Medicare and increasing the minimum wage.
